  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PNG Highlands Joint Programme for Peace and Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project forms a component of a comprehensive UN Joint programme in Papua New Guinea and specifically targets community-based interventions in Hela province. IOM&apos;s activities implemented under this intervention include supporting communities to identify and implement disaster preparedness and risk mitigation measures; restoring/rehabilitating/strengthening and equipping evacuation centres according to safety standards in line with national and local disaster risk reduction strategies; and improving access to clean and safe water through drilling bore holes and/or rehabilitating/installing gravity feed irrigation systems or rainwater catchments systems at schools, health centres and community centres for drinking, washing, and gardening.</narrative>
  </description>
